{"word":"H5258 - נָסַךְ - nâçak - naw-sak' - Cover","slug":"H5258","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָסַךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâçak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-sak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cover"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E1;&#x05DA; - na&#x0302;sak</b> - <i>naw-sak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>pour</i> out, especially a libation, or to <i>cast</i> (metal); by analogy to <i>anoint</i> a king: - cover, melt, offer, (cause to) pour (out), set (up)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5257\">H5257</a>"}]}